What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Chromium Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Chromium Market

Chromium market will expect to grow at a rate of 3.50% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Chromium market report analyses the growth, which is currently being growing due to the rising demand from the stainless steel industry.

Chromium is a chemical component bearing the symbol Cr and is a lustrous and brittle steely-grey. Chromium is a hard metal with properties that are resistant to corrosion. When polished, chromium gains a very shiny surface that is used to plate other metals to produce a protective and appealing coating. In many uses, such as metal ceramics, chrome plating, dyes and paints, alloy-stainless steel, chromium is commonly used as a catalyst for leather dyeing and tanning.

The growing demand of the product due to its superior corrosion resistance properties, rising number of applications in automotive, aerospace, defence, marine, building and construction, and electronics, increasing demand of the product in various chemical processes and metallurgical uses, rapid urbanization as well as industrialization across the globe, surging levels of investment for the development of the infrastructure are some of the major as well as vital factors which will likely to augment the growth of the chromium market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, growing usage of chromium as an element in steel metal for decorative plating in the automotive sector along with adoption of advanced technology which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the chromium market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

Volatility in the prices of raw material along with carcinogenic properties of chromium which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the chromium in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Associated health effect of the product which will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

